OL,4,CPenguin Random House keeps furlough
OL,5,Ccash despite strong sales
OL,6, Britain's biggest publisher says it
OL,7, will not hand back funds it received
OL,8, under the furlough scheme, despite
OL,9, seeing strong sales in lockdown.
OL,11,FPenguin Random House UK is thought to
OL,12,Fhave claimed about #1m via the scheme.
OL,14,FLike other publishers, it has seen
OL,15,Fdemand for books surge as people spend
OL,16,Fmore time at home.
OL,18,FA spokesperson said: "We have used the
OL,19,Fgovernment's furlough scheme for its
OL,20,Fintended purpose: to protect jobs
OL,21,Fduring this extraordinary time."
